# Force LF in the git index for every text file regardless of the
# committer's platform. Prettier is configured with endOfLine: lf, so
# without this our Windows committers' files round-trip as CRLF, the
# Linux CI prettier run flags every line, and `yarn format:check` fails
# on every push. Setting eol=lf here means git checks out LF on Linux
# and CRLF on Windows (working tree), but the index is canonical LF.

* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary types — never normalize. Listing the ones we actually ship so a
# new file extension doesn't accidentally get text-converted.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.pdf binary
*.zip binary
*.gz binary
*.tar binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf binary
*.eot binary
*.otf binary
*.msi binary
*.exe binary
*.dll binary
*.dylib binary
*.so binary
